            Sturgeon says Scottish government 'can't accept brexit deal'
            Scotland' First Minister Nicola Sturgeon has said that no Scottish government could possibly accept a deal which left the country poorer.She made the comment during a news conference in which she outlined her government's opposition to the Brexit deal negotiated by Prime Minister Theresa May.Ms Sturgeon told the gathered media: "As [our] analysis demonstrates this will make Scotland, and indeed the whole of the UK, poorer."
                
                        27 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
